29/04/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Croatian Farmers' Party presented a set of political priorities and objectives Monday (28 April) for the general elections, expected in the fall or early next year. As a key member of the ruling coalition, the party would continue to promote Croatia's accession to the EU and NATO. The programme outlines measures aiming to speed up economic growth, reduce the shadow economy and improve education and social policy.
In other news, Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan visited Zagreb on Monday and pledged that his country would support Croatia's efforts for a quick EU accession procedure. Italy's foreign minister echoed that sentiment during a meeting in Sarajevo with his Croatian counterpart. (Vjesnik - 29/04/03; HINA, HRT - 28/04/03)
